item.title: Hackers target Iran state TV's satellite transmission to broadcast exiled crown prince
item.description: Hackers have disrupted Iranian state television to air footage supporting the exiled crown prince

item.title: Vietnam party meeting opens with leadership and economic growth on the line
item.description: Vietnam’s Communist Party has opened a meeting to decide the country's top leadership and policies for the next five years

item.title: China's economy grows 5% in 2025, buoyed by strong exports despite Trump's tariffs
item.description: China has reported its economy expanded at a 5% annual pace in 2025, buoyed by strong exports despite U.S. President Donald Trump’s tariffs

item.title: Chinese steel factory officials detained after explosion that leaves 2 dead, 8 missing
item.description: Chinese police have detained those in charge of a steel factory in Inner Mongolia after an explosion killed two people

item.title: Hard-right populist wins a place in a two-way runoff in Portugal’s presidential election
item.description: André Ventura, the leader of Portugal's hard-right Chega party, has placed second in the country's presidential election
